column1: ********LEGEND FOR FIELD NAMES LOCATED AT BOTTOM OF FILE************

The best available dataset does not include values where the flag code is <0 (data outside sensor limits; rejected data; missing data; and optional SWMP supported data that were not collected). If you wish to export all this data you must choose the All Inclusive Data button.

Please refer to the Read Me document bundled in the ZIP file for important information regarding data QAQC and data file contents.  After quarterly data QC and submission; an abbreviated metadata document will also be available detailing specific Reserve and station data collection methods; QAQC; and contact information.
A more complete metadata document will be available after the annual round of data QC and submission. After tertiary review a complete
metadata document will also be available detailing specific Reserve and station data collection methods; QAQC; and contact information.
Frequency: 15 minute collection interval.  Prior to 2007; frequencies for 60 (hourly) and 144 (daily) averages were also reported.
ATemp: average air temperature measured in degrees Celsius (C)
RH: average relative humidity measured in percent saturation (%)
BP: average barometric pressure measured in millibars (mb)
WSpd: average wind speed measured in meters per second (m/s)
MaxWSpd: max wind speed measured in meters per second (m/s)
MaxWSpdT: time of max wind speed measurement (hh:mm)

Wdir: average direction from which the wind originates measured in degrees true North as of April 1 2008. Prior to April 1 2008 wind direction was measured with no correction for magnetic declination. See Reserve metadata for exact date of shift to true North.
TotPAR: photosynthetically active radiation measured in millimoles per square meter (total flux integrated – totalized - over each 15-minute logging interval)
TotPrcp: total precipitation measured in millimeters (mm)
TotSoRad: total solar radiation measured in watts per square meter (optional SWMP supported parameter)
NOTE: The average or total (depending on the parameter) data value reported are for the interval prior to the time stamp.
Provisional Plus: A value of 0 in the provisional plus column indicates that the data have been through the automated flagging process (primary QAQC) ONLY and has not been checked by the Reserve.
While a value of 1 in the provisional plus column indicates that the data have been through secondary QAQC at the Reserve using Excel macros (provided by the CDMO) to further QAQC the data.
Historical: A value of 0 in the historical column indicates that the data have not been through final QAQC by the CDMO. A value of 1 indicates that the data have been through
final tertiary review at the CDMO and posted as the final authoritative data.
isSWMP:  A value of P indicates that this is a primary SWMP station and will ultimately go through tertiary review by the CDMO.  A value of S indicates that this is a secondary SWMP station.
Secondary SWMP stations must follow all SWMP SOPs but do not go through tertiary review.
Each SWMP required parameter in the dataset is followed by a flag column (where the parameter header is preceded by a F_).
3         Calculated data: non-vented depth/level sensor correction for changes in barometric pressure
